🤍A druzy is sets of tiny crystals of minerals that form on the surface of another stone.

💛 This occurs when water brings minerals onto a rock's surface.

🤍 When the water evaporates, cooling occurs and the minerals are left behind to form crystals on top of the rock. 

💛 Depending on the minerals, druzy can be almost any color of the rainbow, including white, pink, blue, purple, green, or black.

The formation of the Amethyst is the result of the interaction between aquifers and volcanic activity, leading to the unique and vibrant hues that make Uruguayan amethyst so sought after. It is estimated these crystals are 130-150 million years old!

👉 The Uruguayan Amethyst geode is a promoter of creativity and new ideas, inspiring fresh insights and often divine inspiration.

✨ The combination of both amethyst and stalactites is very rare and found in only a few places in the world like Uruguay.

✨ These formations begin with a single drop of mineral rich water that continues to drip from the roof of the caves.

✨ As the dripping continues, layers of calcite are deposited in rings and over time they settle on top of each other creating the stalactite.  

✨ Once the agate center has formed then the amethyst crystals grow on the outside surface.

✨ Stalactites are then cross cut into these slices to expose a core of interestingly shaped agate surrounded by crystalline amethyst.

👉 Did you know? These are generally thought to be about 130 million years old!
